# ── (2) raw 162 full draft text (R block, ready-to-append to hive .raw) ─
@R raw-162-parallel-blocker-fanout-mandate-full-draft :: meta [4!]
  <- raw-162-parallel-blocker-fanout-mandate-draft-witness
  -> hive-dot-raw-append-target
  => "BEGIN raw 162 draft (canonical hive .raw line format):"
  raw 162 new "parallel-blocker-fanout-mandate - every blocker SSOT entry whose fire-target spans ≥2 independent objectives (axes / repos / sub-agents / hosts) MUST declare fire-parallel-fanout (N>=2 entries, 1-line each) + fire-fanout-deps (DAG edges, empty = full-parallel) + aggregate-resolution-metric so multi-target loops fan out canonically instead of serializing through a single fire-cmd"
    slug parallel-blocker-fanout-mandate
    enforce tool/parallel_fanout_lint.hexa
    enforce-layer hive-agent
    enforce-layer-rationale parse-time SSOT lint over state/blockers/*.hexa entries; detects multi-target blockers (≥2 distinct repo OR ≥2 distinct sub-agent OR ≥2 distinct objective_id) and verifies fire-parallel-fanout+fire-fanout-deps+aggregate-resolution-metric triple is present; algorithm core (multi-target detector + DAG cycle check via raw 79 reuse + schema validator) is a hive-agent runtime executor.
    enforce-layer-secondary os-level
    enforce-layer-secondary-rationale raw 1 chflags + tier2 path-pattern lock on tool/parallel_fanout_lint.hexa and state/blockers/ — lint binary cannot be silently bypassed; immutability inherits raw 45's existing os-lock on state/blockers/.
    enforce-layer-tertiary cli-lint
    enforce-layer-tertiary-rationale ./hexa tool/parallel_fanout_lint.hexa --selftest fixtures (positive: 2-target blocker w/ fanout fields PASS ; negative: 2-target blocker w/o fanout fields FAIL ; cycle: A→B→A FAIL via raw 79 strict ; single-target exempt PASS) gates the lint at tool registration time and on every CI push — distinct from runtime hive-agent enforcement.
    decl tool/parallel_fanout_lint.hexa
    scope every blocker SSOT entry under state/blockers/<slug>.hexa whose fire-target spans ≥2 independent objectives — independence detected via (i) ≥2 distinct repo paths in fire-cwd, OR (ii) ≥2 distinct sub-agent slugs in dispatch-mode subagent agent-list, OR (iii) ≥2 distinct objective_id / axis_id / target_id fields, OR (iv) explicit multi-target=true flag — MUST declare three fields: (a) fire-parallel-fanout = N entries (1-line each, format `<target_id> <fire-cmd>` per entry, N>=2); (b) fire-fanout-deps = DAG edges (`<from_target_id> -> <to_target_id>` per line ; empty block = full-parallel default ; cycles forbidden by raw 79 strict topological sort); (c) aggregate-resolution-metric = boolean aggregator over per-target resolution (default = ALL must flip resolved ; alternates ANY / N-of-M / weighted ; explicit aggregator-op required). single-target blockers (only one objective in fire-cwd × dispatch-mode × objective_id) are scope-EXEMPT — no fanout fields required (counter-example clause). resolution semantics inherit raw 45 omega-blocker-autofire (status active → resolved per witness collector); fanout adds per-target attempt-log split (state/blockers/<slug>.fires/<target_id>/<ts>.log) so per-target convergence is observable.
    why serial firing of a multi-target blocker wastes wall-clock by N× (each tick fires only one target, so N-target blocker takes N ticks minimum to make first contact with all targets) AND admits the "first-cmd-blocks-rest" failure cascade (when target 1's fire-cmd hangs / errors out / pid-locks the slot, targets 2..N never fire under raw 45's single-flight pidfile guard). parallel-canonical fanout removes both: (i) wall-clock reduces from N×interval to max(per-target interval) under raw 79's parallel-DAG scheduler ; (ii) per-target single-flight guards are independent (one target stuck does not block the others). user 2026-04-28 directive 'raw 의 loop raw 개선 필요 위 모두 kick 할수 있도록 병렬로' = make parallel firing the DEFAULT/CANONICAL pattern, not an opt-in. companion to raw 45 RUNTIME enhancement (Agent A in flight) — Agent A patches tool/blocker_autofire.hexa to fan out at execution time ; raw 162 patches the SCHEMA so the SSOT entries declaring multi-target fanout are themselves canonical (orthogonal axes, both required).
    deps raw:omega-blocker-autofire
    deps raw:execution-parallel-DAG-scheduler-witness
    deps raw:subagent-parent-propagation
    deps raw:bottleneck-gap-paradigm-via-nexus-kick
    deps raw:design-novelty-counter-example-5check-mandate
    deps raw:strategy-multi-realizability-mandate
    deps raw:triad-universal-mandate
    proof tool/parallel_fanout_lint.hexa --selftest
    proof raw-162-self-apply-PASS-at-registration (5-check schema_validate + multi-target detector positive/negative/cycle/exempt fixtures)
    measurement-axis parallel-fanout-coverage
    measurement-axis-formula parallel-fanout-coverage = blockers_with_fanout_field_declared / total_multi_target_blockers_detected
    measurement-threshold parallel-fanout-coverage>=0.50-at-30d ; >=0.85-at-90d
    falsifier 30d post-registration parallel-fanout-coverage < 0.50 → retire (mandate ineffective ; multi-target blockers not adopting canonical fields)
    falsifier 3+ legitimate multi-target blockers cannot use fanout (genuinely sequential dependency where target B's fire-cmd requires target A's resolution as input) → exempt clause needed (add fanout-exempt-rationale field)
    falsifier fanout DAG-cycle detected at parse → MUST abort (raw 79 strict topological sort, no cycles permitted)
    realization-channel-1 SSOT-schema-lint (parse state/blockers/*.hexa, detect multi-target via repo/agent/objective heuristics, validate fanout-triple presence)
    realization-channel-2 runtime-fanout-dispatch (raw 45 executor + Agent A enhancement reads fire-parallel-fanout block, spawns N parallel fire-cmds via raw 79 DAG scheduler, attempts-log split per target)
    realization-channel-3 ci-pre-push-gate (./hexa tool/parallel_fanout_lint.hexa --check across all state/blockers/*.hexa, fail push if any multi-target blocker missing fanout fields or contains DAG cycle)
    cognitive-framework-1 fan-out / map-reduce parallelism (Dean & Ghemawat 2004 MapReduce, Lamport 1979 sequential consistency dual)
    cognitive-framework-2 parallel-DAG topological scheduling (raw 79 + Cormen-Leiserson-Rivest-Stein CLRS Ch.22 DFS w/g/b cycle detection + critical-path-method PERT/CPM)
    counter-example single-target blockers — when a blocker has exactly one fire-cmd targeting one objective (e.g., state/blockers/v3_metric_redesign.hexa raw 45 example), fanout fields are NOT required and add only ceremony ; scope-exempt clause prevents over-application
    novelty-falsifier if 30d coverage < 0.50 OR 3+ legitimate exemptions surface OR DAG-cycle false-positives appear → retire/revise (strictly testable disconfirmation criteria, not aspirational)
    paired-roadmap-id 162
    triad-exempt forward-spec-meta-rule
    category routing-dispatch
    applies-to ssot-registration
    phase pre-write
    severity warn
  => "END raw 162 draft (52 contract lines including header)"

